# Catalyst One — Enterprise Workspace UX Standard

Status: **ENTERPRISE APPROVED** · Priority: **CRITICAL** · Scope: **ALL workspaces**

Screen layout, hierarchy, tables, charts, and the Five Second Rule are governed by **Enterprise Design & UX Standard v1.0** (`enterprise-screen-ux-standard.mdc`). This rule covers **workspace chrome** (shell, journey ribbon, Close, unsaved changes).

Do **not** implement screen-by-screen one-offs. Extend shared shell/chrome so every module inherits behaviour.

## Targets

- Chrome (nav + workflow + contextual header) ≤ **~20–25%** of viewport
- Primary work area ≥ **~75–80%**
- Think desktop ERP — maximise working area; minimise empty space and repeated facts

## Shared primitives (use these)

| Primitive | Path |
|---|---|
| `EnterpriseWorkspaceShell` | `src/components/catalyst-one/shared/enterprise-workspace-shell.tsx` |
| `EnterpriseWorkspaceLayout` (CO-SPRINT-106 layers) | `src/components/enterprise/workspace-layout/` |
| `WorkspaceIntelligenceRibbon` (CO-SPRINT-110) | full-width file-scoped CHANAKYA ticker — no pipeline bucket counts |
| `LeadOpportunityJourneyChrome` | `src/components/catalyst-one/shared/lead-opportunity-journey-chrome.tsx` |
| `WorkspaceHeader` + `useWorkspaceClose` | shared header + close API |
| `UnsavedChangesDialog` | Save & Close · Discard · Cancel |
| Constants | `src/constants/enterprise-workspace-ux.ts`, `enterprise-workspace-layout.ts` |

Complex desks (Loan Workspace) must compose **CO-SPRINT-106 layers** via `EnterpriseWorkspaceLayout` — see `enterprise-workspace-layout-standard.mdc`.


## Mandatory rules

1. **Natural page scrolling** — default `scrollMode="document"`. Do not lock route shells with `h-[calc(100vh-4rem)] overflow-hidden` unless a true split desk needs `scrollMode="locked-split"` (rare). Browser/`main` must scroll. **Credit Workbench & Strategic Workspace** must use document scroll; only document preview panes may use min-height + internal overflow.
2. **Workflow ribbon** — Loan Workspace keeps the permanent Business Journey Navigator. **Strategic Workspace** and **Credit Workbench** use `journeyNavigatorMode="button"` (`Workflow Progress ▼` → expandable panel). Do not apply the button pattern to Loan Workspace.
3. **Collapse chrome on scroll** — secondary chrome collapses; keep compact identity + primary actions + **Close**.
4. **No information repetition** — facts already in the header must not be re-carded in Overview / snapshot panels. One business fact once.
5. **Header content** — essential context only (borrower, file/opportunity, product, amount, stage, health, RM) + primary actions.
6. **✕ Close** — every major workspace, upper-right. Wire via `useWorkspaceClose` / chrome `closeTo`.
7. **Close behaviour**
   - Clean → close immediately (optional toast when `acknowledgeCleanClose`)
   - Dirty → Unsaved Changes: **Save & Close** / **Discard** / **Cancel**
   - After save-and-close → toast **All changes saved.**
8. **Keep** Action Center, Chanakya Guide, Transaction Insights, Save, Save & Exit, Navigation — only densify layout.
9. **Future workspaces** must compose `EnterpriseWorkspaceShell` or journey chrome — never invent a third chrome family.

## Anti-patterns

- Fixed-height content traps that stop page scroll
- Duplicate borrower/loan cards under an identity header
- Marketing-style vertical whitespace
- Missing Close on enterprise desks
